UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Austin A30/BMW Isetta: Two British classics head into to the Mathewsons' auction room, Dave heads to North Manchester to pick up an Austin A30 and a Morris 8 E with an alternative paint job. S4 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Secret Nazi Bases
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Kraftwerk Nord West: One of the largest Nazi bunkers ever constructed, outside the French town of Watten, a missile facility with storage for 108 missiles and two launch pads. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Nazi Hunters
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Hunting Adolf Eichmann: Hear about the tireless pursuit of those responsible for atrocities during World War II. Find out how Adolf Eichmann was tracked to Argentina in 1961. S1 Ep10

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Antiques Roadshow
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Broughton Castle 2: Fiona Bruce presents from Broughton Castle in Oxfordshire, where items brought in for valuation include two 18th-century paintings depicting the house's servants. S39 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Operation Arctic with Simon Reeve
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Life in Polar Bear Town: Gordon Buchanan visits Churchill, Manitoba, a Canadian town that for two months of every year is inundated by polar bears making their journey north. S1 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Flipping Bangers
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: New. Volvo: Will and Gus lay their hands on a potentially very valuable Volvo. It's great to look at, but doesn't start easily and cannot stop. S1 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash: Restoring Classics
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Daimler / Triumph 2000: Derek points the team towards one of his favourite motors - a 1983 Daimler Double Six. And a Triumph 2000 is given a modern day makeover under the bonnet. S7 Ep1
